<div id="review_2919599627" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2919599627" />
    <a title="Brian Blickenstaff" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4311824-brian-blickenstaff"><img alt="Brian Blickenstaff" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1544600013p2/4311824.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2919599627?book_show_action=true">Aug 01, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Brian Blickenstaff" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Brian Blickenstaff" href="/user/show/4311824-brian-blickenstaff">Brian Blickenstaff</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780140184624" href="/book/show/954637.Isaac_Babel">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4311824-brian-blickenstaff?shelf=short-stories">short-stories</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2919599627" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3236560401692218583">This is a weird one. What narrative exists can be hard to follow but the writing is so full of style that you can see why Babel still gets name checked a lot. His descriptive writing is incredible. Very much a writer&apos;s writer. <br/><br/>I wouldn&apos;t recommend it unless you&apos;re super caught up on your history of the Russian Revolution and WWI. I am not exactly a Russian history buff and that def colored my opinion here. But for those of you who do read it, a couple of pro tips: 1) Get yourself a good map of P</span>
  <span id="freeText3236560401692218583" style="display:none">This is a weird one. What narrative exists can be hard to follow but the writing is so full of style that you can see why Babel still gets name checked a lot. His descriptive writing is incredible. Very much a writer's writer. <br /><br />I wouldn't recommend it unless you're super caught up on your history of the Russian Revolution and WWI. I am not exactly a Russian history buff and that def colored my opinion here. But for those of you who do read it, a couple of pro tips: 1) Get yourself a good map of Poland/Ukraine. 2) Keep notes on the different characters. The stories aren't really short stories in the contemporary sense but rather short scenes from the war, and they're not in chronological order. Notes would help keep it all straight.</span>
  <a data-text-id="3236560401692218583" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
