<div id="review_2443528394" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2443528394" />
    <a title="Kallie" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2400951-kallie"><img alt="Kallie" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1249764384p2/2400951.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2443528394?book_show_action=true">Nov 01, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kallie" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kallie" href="/user/show/2400951-kallie">Kallie</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780140184624" href="/book/show/954637.Isaac_Babel">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2400951-kallie?shelf=short-stories">short-stories</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2443528394" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2028612344233803198">This collection took me a long time because Babel cannot be read quickly. The rich, somewhat surreal detail of his prose must be savored slowly, for me a few pages at a time. How he manages to write of the horrors he witnessed, yet write with such humor, is a literary miracle. Several times, contemporary writers I tried to read at the same time suffered so much by comparison, I had to put them aside. I feel much more knowledgeable about Eastern European and Hebraic culture now, after reading the</span>
  <span id="freeText2028612344233803198" style="display:none">This collection took me a long time because Babel cannot be read quickly. The rich, somewhat surreal detail of his prose must be savored slowly, for me a few pages at a time. How he manages to write of the horrors he witnessed, yet write with such humor, is a literary miracle. Several times, contemporary writers I tried to read at the same time suffered so much by comparison, I had to put them aside. I feel much more knowledgeable about Eastern European and Hebraic culture now, after reading these stories. And I might be able to tackle Ulysses again. Joyce, in Ulysses, is the writer most comparable for me, not in subject matter but style.</span>
  <a data-text-id="2028612344233803198" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

