  <span id="freeText12695885159585414740" style="display:none">For the first two-thirds of this book I was convinced somehow that Babel's brutal world of thuggish amorality would be preferable to my own, I think because it involved horses, was set in central Europe and described by Babel. Then he gets into his childhood and the pogroms in the last third of the book and it was so grotesquely horrifying that I wouldn't trade places with his characters for the world, no way, I've had enough of childhood thank you, although mine wasn't so bad I guess since no one beat me with a sack of pigeons.</span>
