<div id="review_13094648" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/13094648" />
    <a title="Jeff Jackson" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/811567-jeff-jackson"><img alt="Jeff Jackson" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1531248217p2/811567.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/13094648?book_show_action=true">Jan 21, 2008</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jeff Jackson" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jeff Jackson" href="/user/show/811567-jeff-jackson">Jeff Jackson</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780452007987" href="/book/show/1620533.Babel_The_Collected_Stories_of_Isaac">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer13094648" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8463657217151689094">The Walter Morrison translation is the one you want. The new Norton editions are handsome and worth owning for hardcore fans but the translations are a bit clunky. Newcomers should start here to discover why Babel is such a great short story writer in modes ranging from bawdy stories about Odessa, caustic fables, laugh out loud sketches about the foibles of politics and love, poetic evocations of youth, and harrowingly bleak stories of wartime. </span>

          </span>
        </div>


